==English==
===Etymology===
from Greek ολιγοι (''oligoi'') 'few' + αρχ- (''arkh-'') 'to rule'
===Pronunciation===
(US) IPA: /ˈoʊlɪˌgɑrk/
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# a [[member]] of an [[oligarchy]], someone who is part of a [[small]] [[group]] that runs a country
# a very [[rich]] person (especially in Russia)

====Translations====
*French: [[oligarque]]

